      • referenceEndInterpolationMonth

        public InflationEndInterpolatedRateObservation.Builder referenceEndInterpolationMonth(YearMonth referenceEndInterpolationMonth)
        Sets the reference month used for interpolation for the index relative to the end of the period.

        The reference month for interpolation is typically one month after the reference end month. As such it is typically two months before the accrual end date. Must be after the reference end month.

        Parameters:
        referenceEndInterpolationMonth - the new value, not null
        Returns:
        this, for chaining, not null

      • weight

        public InflationEndInterpolatedRateObservation.Builder weight(double weight)
        Sets the positive weight used when interpolating.

        Given two price index observations, typically in adjacent months, the weight is used to determine the adjusted index value. The value is given by the formula (weight * price_index_1 + (1 - weight) * price_index_2).

        Parameters:
        weight - the new value
        Returns:
        this, for chaining, not null
